    "body": "Replace 6 bare `assert` statements in `test/functional/wallet_bumpfee.py` with test framework helpers (`assert_greater_than`, `assert_equal`).\n\nBare asserts produce unhelpful `AssertionError` with no context on failure. The helpers print actual vs expected values.\n\n**Changes:**\n- `assert bumped_tx[\"fee\"] > -rbftx[\"fee\"]` → `assert_greater_than`\n- `assert bumped_psbt[\"fee\"] > -rbftx[\"fee\"]` → `assert_greater_than`\n- `assert len(oldwtx[\"walletconflicts\"]) > 0` → `assert_greater_than`\n- `assert len(bumpedwtx[\"details\"]) == 1` → `assert_equal`\n- `assert bumpedwtx[\"details\"][0][\"address\"] == new_address` → `assert_equal`\n- `assert rbf_node.getbalance() < 49` → `assert_greater_than(49, ...)`\n\nNo new imports needed — all helpers already imported. Each replacement preserves the exact same logical condition.\n\nPart of #23119.",
